      "caseOverview": "The dispute involves the construction of the Palmetto Ridge Medical Office Building between Palmetto Ridge Development, LLC (Owner) and Keystone Building Group, Inc. (Contractor). The conflict centers around delays allegedly caused by late RFI responses, owner-directed design changes, and delayed owner-furnished equipment deliveries. Keystone is claiming an extension of 94 days and additional compensation of $1,847,000, which the Owner disputes, citing contractual notice periods and clauses precluding damages for delays. The current posture includes an Owner's formal letter denying the Contractor's claim.",
